<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="6" pageNumber="443" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1841,2012]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,578]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="6" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1878,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="443">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Ivory, boldly striped with dark brown across tylus, crown and twice across eyes, twice on anterior margin of pronotum, and with 
<number box="[493,507,1915,1938]" pageId="6" pageNumber="443" value="7.0">7</number>
longitudinal stripes extending backwards, with only median line meeting posterior transverse band; scutellum and base of tegmen black with contrasting yellow ridges on scutellum and second claval vein, ivory between vein bases; rest of tegmen hyaline with dark brown veins (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1142,1987,2012]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[165,1405,205,1746]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1753]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Examples of Clastopterinae (10 – 11) and Machaerotinae (12 – 16). 10, Clastoptera testacea Fitch; 11, Iba cuneata Schmidt, lectotype; 12, Allox transfigurata; 13, Metaenderleinia nervosa Lallemand; 14, Machaeropsis dramatica (genital capsule as in Metaenderleinia); 15, Irridiculum; 16, Hindoloides bipunctata (Haupt), male genitalia typical of Machaerotini and Hindoloidini. A, habitus; B, male genital capsule (small styles as in 16 B omitted in 12 – 13 B). Scale line for habitus drawings: 1 mm (Fig. 11 A slightly larger)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227825/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="443">
Fig. 
<number box="[1113,1142,1988,2012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="443" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
A); underside with brown stripes on frontal arcs, across gena, and on pleura just below costa of folded tegmina; midline of face broadly black with oval orange disc near tip of head; legs with 
<number box="[711,725,189,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" value="2.0">2</number>
longitudinal bands on femur, 
<number box="[1068,1082,189,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" value="2.0">2</number>
transverse bands on tibia, tarsi black with pale marks towards tip of each tarsomere on upper surface. Ovipositor blade 
<quantity box="[1166,1255,225,249]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
long, a third as wide as long, dorsal margin straight but shallowly emarginate at middle for half its length, tip bluntly pointed (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 17 A – R" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1434,1456]" captionTargetBox="[314,1259,193,1398]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[313,1273,193,1412]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 17 A – R. Ovipositor shapes in 17 genera and subgenera of Clastopteridae: Zygonini (A, G – J, Q), Machaerotinae (B – D, K, R) and Clastopterinae (E, F, L – Q). A, Zygon desegregatum, paratype; B, Irridiculum deformatum, holotype; C, Allox transfigurata, paratype; D, Taiorhina geisha Schumacher; E, Grellaphia costalis Schmidt; F, Beesoniella sylvestris Lallemand; G, Pseudomachaerota olivacea, holotype; H, Ambonga lanceolata; J, Hemizygon saturnus (as in Ambonga apicenotata); K. Machaeropsis dramatica; L, Tremapterus (Nyanja) bimaculata Synave, holotype; M, Tremapterus (Abbalomba) typica Distant; N, Tremapterus (Patriziana) janus Linnavuori; O, Tremapterus (s. s.) rufus (Thunberg); P, Sepullia fuscolimbata Lallemand; Q, Pseudoclastoptera irrubesco; R, Machaerota sp. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227826/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="444">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,298,322]" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" value="17.0">17</number>
K
</figureCitation>
). Length: male 5.0– 
<quantity box="[429,516,298,323]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
; female 
<quantity box="[610,699,298,323]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
