<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="444" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,480,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="444">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species keys to the type-species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Melichar" authorityName="Melichar" box="[886,1101,480,505]" class="Insecta" family="Machaerotidae" genus="Machaeropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis box="[886,993,480,505]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="444">M. valida</emphasis>
Melichar
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1168,1249,480,505]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="444">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maa" box="[1263,1380,480,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" refString="Maa, T. C. (1963) A review of the Machaerotidae (Hemiptera: Cercopoidea). Pacific Insects Monograph, 5, 1 - 166." type="journal article" year="1963">
Maa 
<number box="[1321,1380,480,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but has the heiroglyphic markings of the dorsum as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Maa" authorityName="Maa" box="[712,946,517,542]" class="Insecta" family="Machaerotidae" genus="Machaeropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrolineata">
<emphasis box="[712,890,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="444">M. rubrolineata</emphasis>
Maa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1012,1115,517,542]" name="Thailand" pageId="7" pageNumber="444">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. The markings, however, are blackish rather than red.
</paragraph>
